{"title":"Add experimental conditions to multi-well plates","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Add experimental conditions to multi-well plates","date":"2022-09-02","description":"Tools for interacting with data from experiments done in microtiter plates. Easily read in plate-shaped data and convert it to tidy format, combine plate-shaped data with tidy data, and view tidy data in plate shape.","image":"f1.jpg","categories":["plater","R"]},"headingText":"check_plater_format(\"data/palter.csv\", sep = \",\")","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{r setup, include=FALSE}\nknitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.width = 6, fig.height = 3.8,\n                      fig.align = \"center\", fig.retina = 3,\n                      out.width = \"85%\", collapse = TRUE)\n```\n\n\n```{r}\nlibrary(plater)\n```\n\n```{r}\nTreatment <- read_plates(\"plater1.csv\",\n    plate_names = \"ZG22006\",\n    well_ids_column = \"Well.ID\"\n)\nTreatment\n\nGroup <- read_plates(\"plater2.csv\",\n    plate_names = \"ZG22006\",\n    well_ids_column = \"Well.ID\"\n)\nGroup\n```\n\n## Reference\n\n1. [From a million nested ifelses to the plater package](https://ropensci.org/blog/2017/02/06/plater-blog-post)\n2. [Getting started with plater](https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/plater/vignettes/plater-basics.html)\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n```{r setup, include=FALSE}\nknitr::opts_chunk$set(fig.width = 6, fig.height = 3.8,\n                      fig.align = \"center\", fig.retina = 3,\n                      out.width = \"85%\", collapse = TRUE)\n```\n\n\n```{r}\nlibrary(plater)\n```\n\n```{r}\n# check_plater_format(\"data/palter.csv\", sep = \",\")\nTreatment <- read_plates(\"plater1.csv\",\n    plate_names = \"ZG22006\",\n    well_ids_column = \"Well.ID\"\n)\nTreatment\n\nGroup <- read_plates(\"plater2.csv\",\n    plate_names = \"ZG22006\",\n    well_ids_column = \"Well.ID\"\n)\nGroup\n```\n\n## Reference\n\n1. [From a million nested ifelses to the plater package](https://ropensci.org/blog/2017/02/06/plater-